<h3>7B. Configure the Project With Your Block</h3>
<p>Open the platform of choice. Create a new Project, Custom GPT, or Gem. Paste the style block as the system prompt or instructions. Save. Test by starting a new chat inside that container and asking for a 300-word draft on any topic.</p>
<h3>7C. Pin a Backup in Plain Text</h3>
<p>Save the style block in a Google Doc, Notion page, or Markdown file outside the LLM. If the platform changes its interface or loses your settings, you keep the asset. Treat it like a brand guideline document. Because that is what it is.</p>
<p><strong>Why this step matters:</strong> Persistence is what makes the system work daily. Without a saved Project or GPT, you spend 5 minutes re-loading instructions every session. With persistence, you start every draft already in voice.</p>
